        <!-- Overview Section -->
        <section id="overview" class="mb-12">
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-blue-700">Navigating the New 2025 Local Rules</h1>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-4">
                    Effective September 1, 2025, the Walla Walla County Superior Court will implement a substantially revised set of Local Rules. This website provides a comprehensive guide for attorneys and legal staff to understand these critical updates.
                </p>
                <p class="text-gray-600">
                    The 2025 amendments introduce new procedures for remote access and digital evidence, restructure entire sections for clarity, and refine existing rules across civil, criminal, and special proceedings. This analysis is designed to help you seamlessly adapt your practice to the new legal landscape in Walla Walla County.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Detailed Analysis Section -->
        <section id="analysis" class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold section-title">Comprehensive Analysis of Changes</h2>
            
            <div class="space-y-8">
                <!-- General Rules -->
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-blue-600">Local General Rules (WWLGR)</h3>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg">WWLGR 2 - Remote Access to Court Proceedings</h4>
                            <p><span class="font-semibold text-green-600">NEW:</span> This is a completely new rule, formalizing procedures for remote court appearances. The 2022 rules had this section reserved.</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 text-gray-600">
                                <li>Specifies who can appear remotely (parties, attorneys, law enforcement, etc.).</li>
                                <li>Mandates clear identification for all remote participants.</li>
                                <li>Establishes technical and decorum requirements.</li>
                                <li>Requires prior court approval for using alternative remote access platforms.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg">WWLGR 14 - Format for Pleadings, Other Papers, and Submission of Digital Exhibits</h4>
                            <p><span class="font-semibold text-green-600">NEW:</span> This rule significantly expands on formatting requirements and introduces a formal process for submitting digital evidence.</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 text-gray-600">
                                <li>Defines "digital exhibits" and mandates a "Notice of Digital Exhibit Declaration."</li>
                                <li>Outlines procedures for service, bench copies, and in-court presentation.</li>
                                <li>Addresses the post-case destruction of digital exhibits.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Civil Rules -->
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-blue-600">Local Civil Rules (WWLCR)</h3>
                     <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg">WWLCR 16 - Pre-Trial Procedure</h4>
                            <p><span class="font-semibold text-yellow-600">MODIFIED:</span> The 2025 rule clarifies that settlement conference position statements "shall not be filed in the court file," reinforcing their confidentiality.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg">WWLCR 47 - Juries</h4>
                            <p><span class="font-semibold text-yellow-600">MODIFIED:</span> The jury selection process is refined. The new rule mandates that court staff provide a seating chart and specifies the timing and procedure for "Batson" challenges, directing the court to follow GR 37.</p>
                        </div>
                         <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg">WWLCR 51 - Instructions to Jury and Deliberations</h4>
                            <p><span class="font-semibold text-yellow-600">MODIFIED:</span> Adds specific formatting requirements for jury instructions (8.5"x11" paper, one-inch margins, 12-point Times New Roman or similar font, double-spaced).</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Criminal and Special Proceedings -->
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-blue-600">Criminal & Special Proceedings Rules</h3>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg">WWLCrR 3.3 - Time for Trial and Case Scheduling</h4>
                            <p><span class="font-semibold text-green-600">NEW:</span> This rule establishes clear timelines for status hearings in criminal cases based on custody status and formalizes the process for scheduling trials and omnibus hearings.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg">WWLSPR 90.04 - Domestic Relations</h4>
                            <p><span class="font-semibold text-red-600">RESTRUCTURED:</span> The former "Walla Walla Local Domestic Relations Rules (WWLDRR)" are now part of the new "Walla Walla Local Special Proceedings Rules (WWLSPR)".</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 text-gray-600">
                                <li><span class="font-semibold text-green-600">NEW Page Limits:</span> A 20-page limit is introduced for declarations, affidavits, and exhibits in support of motions and responses.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold text-green-600">NEW Status Hearings:</span> Mandatory status hearings are now required in all contested domestic relations cases, scheduled approximately six months after filing.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold text-yellow-600">MODIFIED Restraining Order:</span> The automatic mutual restraining order now includes a provision preventing parents from making negative comments about each other to their children.</li>
                                <li><span class="font-semibold text-yellow-600">MODIFIED Mediation Deadline:</span> Mandatory mediation must now be completed at least 30 days before trial.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Key Changes Section -->
        <section id="key-changes" class="mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold section-title">Key Changes at a Glance</h2>
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                <ul class="space-y-4">
                    <li class="flex items-start">
                        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-green-500 mr-3 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path></svg>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg">Technology Integration</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600">Formal rules for remote appearances and digital exhibit submission are now in place.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start">
                        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-green-500 mr-3 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path></svg>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg">Procedural Strictness</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600">New page limits and scheduling deadlines in domestic relations and criminal cases require careful attention.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start">
                        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-green-500 mr-3 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path></svg>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg">Enhanced Pre-Trial Process</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600">Mandatory status hearings in domestic cases will necessitate earlier and more comprehensive case preparation.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="flex items-start">
                        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-green-500 mr-3 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path></svg>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg">Rule Reorganization</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600">Domestic relations rules are now under the new "Special Proceedings" section, requiring familiarity with the new structure.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

